Bonjour à toutes et à tous,

Ci-dessus une offre de PostDoc.

Bien cordialement,
L. Berti et N. Novelli

==================================
*Postdoc: Machine learning workflows and LLMs for enhancing healthcare 
decision-making *

* Position: Post-Doctoral fellow
* Time commitment: Full-time
* Starting date: Flexible from October 2023 or thereafter
* Duration: from 6 to 8 months
* Indicative salary: depending on experience from 2 082,39 Euros to 2 
440,99 Euros net per month (2 591,00 Euros to 3 037,20 Euros gross per 
month) with social security benefits

* Hosting lab: LIS Lab (CNRS UMR 7020), Aix-Marseille University, 
Marseille, South of France
* How to apply: Send your complete CV including a full publication list 
(and if possible a link to your web pages & PhD thesis) to 
noel.novelli@lis-lab.fr and laure.berti@ird.fr

The work will be carried out in the context of QualiHealth, a 
multi-partner project recently funded by ANR (the French Agency for 
Research). The candidate will participate in the research project for 
enhancing the quality of healthcare data.

*  The successful candidate will work to integrate machine learning 
workflows and  LLMs in the context of healthcare application scenarios. 
Specifically, the main missions are:
(i) Research and literature review on scientific workflows and LLMs;
(ii) Designing orchestration algorithms combining machine learning 
workflows and LLMs;
(iii) Prototyping and testing the solutions for various scenarios with 
healthcare data;
(iv) Writing scientific papers.

* Required Profile:
- PhD in Computer Science
- Experience in machine learning and complex data analysis and/or data 
management /mining
- Programming skills in Python
- Good written and verbal communication skills in English
==================================

